author: Shirley Li
title: Ben Affleck and Matt Damon’s ‘Incorporated’ canceled after one season
text:
Ken Woroner/Syfy 
Syfy has canceled Incorporated , its freshman drama executive-produced by Matt Damon and Ben Affleck. 
The series explored a futuristic world in which society is divided between the wealthy business-run Green Zone and the poor Red Zone after climate change has turned most of the population into refugees. Created by David and Alex Pastor, Incorporated followed Ben (Sean Teale), a man from the Red Zone who infiltrated the Green to save a loved one and take down a powerful corporation. 
Ted Humphrey served as showrunner, with Damon and Affleck’s Pearl Street Films partner Jennifer Todd also an executive producer. 
The show starred Teale, Allison Miller, Julia Ormond, and Dennis Haysbert. Deadline first reported the news. Show Full Article
